Earlier this year before she addressed parliament about the issue Daily Mail Australia spoke to Lucy Haslam, Daniel's mother, about the relief that marijuana has brought to her son's life.

Mrs Haslam, a retired nurse, and her husband Lou, a former police officer, have watched their son Daniel deteriorate from a fit and high achieving student to a frail and depressed young man. 

In a speech that Mrs Haslam delivered to Parliament House in Canberra in June, she detailed how her youngest son desperately clings to the hope and relief that illegal cannabis offers him.

While Daniel continues his four year fight with cancer, the effects of chemotherapy have been detrimental.

