Cannabis provides solace for Daniel, unlike others such as antiemetic drugs which are supposed to relieve him from nausea and vomiting induced by cancer treatment.

Mrs Haslam told ABC on Tuesday she was beside herself when she was notified of Mr Baird's decision.

'I think I gave him a big hug and a kiss. He's a very kind, caring man, you know he's a dad,' she said.

'I think he probably knows as any parent the horrible feeling of watching your child suffer and feeling powerless. He can empathise with that I think,' Mrs Haslam added.

